Initializing optimization. For the approximation of existing data sets by D-strip models we must ï¬nd an initial ruled strip model which is subsequently optimized towards developability. It has already been mentioned that a D-strip model is a semi-discrete analogue of a network of conjugate curves, and at the same time an analogue of a PQ mesh (cf. Liu et al. [2006] and Pottmann et al. [2007]). This leads to different ways of initializing strip models:

